Last week at my day job we had a major email incident. None of our email customers could send email while being off network. Meaning if they sent an email on their phone or tablet on a cellular network or another network the SMTP would get blocked. I believe my predecessor incorrectly set up email and anti spam by using the email security gateway also the SMTP gateway. This error only came to light as I believe we were originally running in a “bugged” state. This is good in an enterprise scenario as it protects employee emails. It is bad in a service provider’s scenario as you might imagine why. The executives want email working “now” but in that above configuration it is impossible.
